Canadian Grand Prix Restarts After Rain Delay; Lewis Hamilton Crashes Out

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-06-12T19:50:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/canadian-grand-prix-restarts-after-rain-delay-lewis-hamilton-crashes-out.html
Today’s Canadian Formula One Grand
Prix in  Montreal  was re-started on the 25th lap of a scheduled
70 after a suspension of more than two hours because of rain.
Red Bull’s Sebastian Vettel was in the lead.  Lewis Hamilton  of McLaren crashed out on the eighth lap
after colliding with his teammate Jenson Button.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  